<section id="commands.groups.charges"><title>Charges Commands</title>
	
	<para>Assign partial charges to models, atoms, and patterns.</para>

	<section id="command.ref.charge"><title>charge</title>
		<indexterm><primary>commands</primary><secondary>charge</secondary></indexterm>
		
		<para><emphasis>Syntax:</emphasis></para>
		<funcsynopsis>
			<funcprototype>
				<funcdef>double <function>charge</function></funcdef>
				<void>
			</funcprototype>
			<funcprototype>
				<funcdef>double <function>charge</function></funcdef>
				<paramdef>double <parameter>q</parameter></paramdef>
			</funcprototype>
		</funcsynopsis>
		<para>Assigns a charge of <emphasis>q</emphasis> to each selected atom in the current model, or returns the total charge of the current selection if no value is supplied.</para>
		
		<para>For example:</para>
		<synopsis>
			charge(1.0);
		</synopsis>
		<para>gives each atom in the current model's selection a charge of 1.0.</para>
		
	</section>
	
	<section id="command.ref.chargeff"><title>chargeff</title>
		<indexterm><primary>commands</primary><secondary>chargeff</secondary></indexterm>
		
		<para><emphasis>Syntax:</emphasis></para>
		<funcsynopsis>
			<funcprototype>
				<funcdef>void <function>charge</function></funcdef>
				<void>
			</funcprototype>
		</funcsynopsis>
		<para>Assigns charges to all atoms in the current model based on the forcefield associated to the model and the current types of the atoms.</para>
		
		<para>For example:</para>
		<synopsis>
			chargeff();
		</synopsis>
	
	</section>
	
	<section id="command.ref.chargefrommodel"><title>chargefrommodel</title>
		<indexterm><primary>commands</primary><secondary>chargefrommodel</secondary></indexterm>
		
		<para><emphasis>Syntax:</emphasis></para>
		<funcsynopsis>
			<funcprototype>
				<funcdef>void <function>chargefrommodel</function></funcdef>
				<void>
			</funcprototype>
		</funcsynopsis>
		<para>Copies charges of all atoms in the current model to the atoms of the current trajectory frame.</para>
		
		<para>For example:</para>
		<synopsis>
			chargefrommodel();
		</synopsis>
	
	</section>
	
	<section id="command.ref.chargepatom"><title>chargepatom</title>
		<indexterm><primary>commands</primary><secondary>chargepatom</secondary></indexterm>
		
		<para><emphasis>Syntax:</emphasis></para>
		<funcsynopsis>
			<funcprototype>
				<funcdef>void <function>chargepatom</function></funcdef>
				<paramdef>int <parameter>id</parameter></paramdef>
				<paramdef>double <parameter>q</parameter></paramdef>
			</funcprototype>
		</funcsynopsis>
		<para>Assigns a charge of <emphasis>q</emphasis> to atom <emphasis>id</emphasis> in each molecule of the current pattern.</para>
		
		<para>For example:</para>
		<synopsis>
			chargepatom(3, 0.1);
		</synopsis>
		<para>assigns a charge of 0.1 to the third atom in each molecule of the current pattern.</para>
	
	</section>
	
	<section id="command.ref.chargetype"><title>chargetype</title>
		<indexterm><primary>commands</primary><secondary>chargetype</secondary></indexterm>
		
		<para><emphasis>Syntax:</emphasis></para>
		<funcsynopsis>
			<funcprototype>
				<funcdef>void <function>chargetype</function></funcdef>
				<paramdef>string <parameter>fftype</parameter></paramdef>
				<paramdef>double <parameter>q</parameter></paramdef>
			</funcprototype>
		</funcsynopsis>
		<para>Assigns a charge of <emphasis>q</emphasis> to each atom that is of type <emphasis>fftype</emphasis> in the current model.</para>
		
		<para>For example:</para>
		<synopsis>
			chargetype(&quot;OW&quot;,-0.8);
		</synopsis>
		<para>gives a charge of -0.8 to every atom that has an assigned typename of 'OW'.</para>
	
	</section>
	
	<section id="command.ref.clearcharges"><title>clearcharges</title>
		<indexterm><primary>commands</primary><secondary>clearcharges</secondary></indexterm>
		
		<para><emphasis>Syntax:</emphasis></para>
		<funcsynopsis>
			<funcprototype>
				<funcdef>void <function>clearcharges</function></funcdef>
				<void>
			</funcprototype>
		</funcsynopsis>
		<para>Clears all charges in the current model, setting them to zero.</para>
		
		<para>For example:</para>
		<synopsis>
			clearcharges();
		</synopsis>

	</section>

</section>